line_1: With Conquest flush'd new Wars the Lamprey breaths,
line_2: In prouder State her silver Volumes wreaths:
Fair Science trims her blasted wreaths;

line_1: From every part the scented unguent breathes;
line_2: The purple fillet round my temples wreathes,

line_1: As SCULPTURE speaks, and heavenly MUSIC breathes,
line_2: For thee exulting she entwines the wreaths,
